events.title: Indoor Cycling
events.description: Increase your cardio and strength with our indoor cycling class. Get your heart pumping with a series of sprints, hills, and drills to build endurance, burn calories and relieve stress. This multi-level class will motivate you through music and moves that allow you to set the intensity of your workout and cruise at your own pace.

events.title: Women's Only: Strength 101
events.description: Have you hit a plateau or feel like you’re not getting any stronger? Our expert trainers will guide you through the steps to achieve your strength goals with a dynamic and strength targeted workouts. We will use a variety of exercises and state of the art equipment in our Strength and Conditioning Center.  Challenge yourself in a supportive and motivating environment and achieve your fitness goals with our invigorating strength class.  No matter your fitness level, this is a perfect class to learn the proper technique, fine tune your strength training program, or take it to the next level as an experienced lifter.

events.title: Hatha Yoga
events.description: This gentle class begins with a guided meditation, introduces yoga postures to stretch and strengthen the body, and teaches relaxation practices to reduce stress and calm the mind. Taught in a supportive environment, this 45-minute class is ideal for beginners, but all levels are welcome. Yoga mats are provided.

events.title: Flow Yoga
events.description: Energize your day with our Flow Yoga class. Move seamlessly through poses synchronizing the breath to movement while elevating your heart rate for this total body mindful workout.

events.title: RAWC W.O.D
events.description: Are you new to fitness and exercise? Worried about hurting yourself or using machines incorrectly? Want to get started but don’t know how? Then join us for a RAWC Workout of the Day led by our certified personal trainers. Learn the proper technique and a variety of exercises to add to your own workouts. From dumbbells to barbells, no matter what your fitness goal is… we got you covered!

events.title: Women On Weights
events.description: A class that caters to women's needs and wants! Providing a safe space to get energized while building up strength and muscle. Push yourself and raise your limits with our women focused circuit training using a mix of cardio and weights. An inclusive, fun, and supportive environment that will teach you effective exercises and challenge you to reach your goals.

events.title: Pilates

Perfect for all fitness levels, this dynamic session merges the grace and rhythm of Kathak—an ancient Indian dance—with a full-body workout. Master intricate footwork, spins, and hand gestures while boosting cardiovascular endurance, strength, and flexibility. Whether you're a dance lover or new to fitness, this class offers a fun, engaging way to stay active and connect with your peers.

events.title: Bootcamp
events.description: A high-intensity class that incorporates plyometrics, strength and interval training. Build your cardiovascular and muscular endurance using various types of equipment and bodyweight movements. Challenge yourself and get ready for a top to bottom workout.

events.title: Coached Swim
events.description: The UTM Coached Swim is a program for individuals seeking a gym alternative for fitness, focusing on training for triathlons and competitive swimming. The program is designed to enhance competitive swimming abilities, stroke techniques and personal fitness. Team spirit is encouraged through the occasional organization of social events and regular participation.

events.title: Intro to Coached Swim
events.description: The UTM Intro to Coached Swim program is for individuals seeking a gym alternative for fitness, those training for triathlons, and competitive swimming training who might have limited coached environment experience. This program will introduce the structure of a coached swim and provide a challenging workout for those new to the coached environment. Participants must be able to swim a minimum of 25m and be comfortable in deep water.The program is being introduced to all RAWC Members as part of their membership.

events.title: Flow Yoga

Then join us for a RAWC Workout of the Day led by our certified personal trainers. Learn the proper technique and a variety of exercises to add to your own workouts. From dumbbells to barbells, no matter what your fitness goal is… we got you covered!

events.title: Black Learn to Swim
events.description: Black Learn to Swim is an introductory program for Black identified students designed to focus on water safety and building your confidence in an aquatic environment - all skill levels are welcome! Our aquatic instructors will meet you at your current swimming level and work with you to develop and enhance your skills. Whether you’re conquering floats and glides or beginning to learn your strokes, come by, say hi, and let us help you meet your swimming goals! We offer a Soul Cap and body cream during this swim.

events.title: Cycle Core
events.description: This class offers a fusion experience of traditional high intensity indoor cycling with implementation of core exercises to fire up your whole body! Get registered today to improve your cardiovascular and core endurance, and strength.

events.title: Women's Only: Cardio HIIT
events.description: A 45-minute-high intensity interval training class for all fitness levels. Use a variety of cardiovascular and resistance training equipment such as Ski Ergs, Rowers, Curve Treadmills, weights and more to build cardiovascular and muscular endurance.

events.title: Women on Weights
events.description: A class that caters to women's needs and wants! Providing a safe space to get energized while building up strength and muscle. Push yourself and raise your limits with our women focused circuit training using a mix of cardio and weights. An inclusive, fun, and supportive environment that will teach you effective exercises and challenge you to reach your goals.

events.title: Women's Only: Beginner Boxing

Join this fun session to stay in shape and build your confidence!This class is open to female identifying members.

events.title: Standup Paddleboard

Our aquatic instructors will meet you at your current swimming level and work with you to develop and enhance your skills. Whether you’re conquering floats and glides or beginning to learn your strokes, come by, say hi, and let us help you meet your swimming goals!

events.title: Stroke Development
events.description: Are you looking to get some guidance on improving your strokes? This program will allow you to get feedback on your strokes and ideas to help make improvements. Staff will watch your strokes and provide drills to help you fine tune your strokes. Note: This is not a lesson.

events.title: Adaptive Fitness Swim
events.description: Join us in the far right lanes for accessible options for those with physical limitations requiring use of our PAL lift. Participants who need assistance transferring or swimming must bring support with them.

events.title: Coached Swim
events.description: The UTM Coached Swim is a program for individuals seeking a gym alternative for fitness, focusing on training for triathlons and competitive swimming. The program is designed to enhance competitive swimming abilities, stroke techniques and personal fitness. Team spirit is encouraged through the occasional organization of social events and regular participation.

events.title: Intro to Coached Swim
events.description: The UTM Intro to Coached Swim program is for individuals seeking a gym alternative for fitness, those training for triathlons, and competitive swimming training who might have limited coached environment experience. The program is designed to enhance competitive swimming abilities, stroke techniques, and personal fitness. This program will introduce the structure of a coached swim and provide a challenging workout for those new to the coached environment. Participants must be able to swim a minimum of 25m and be comfortable in deep water.The program is being introduced to all RAWC Members as part of their membership.

announcements.title: RAWC Closed: Winter Break
announcements.body:
The UTM Recreation, Athletics & Wellness Centre will close at **4:00 p.m. on Monday, December 23rd 2024** and **will reopen at 10:00 a.m. on Saturday, January 4th 2025**. If you have a rented locker, you are encouraged to retrieve your belongings *before* December 23rd, since lockers will not be accessible during the winter closure. We wish you all a safe and healthy holiday season, and look forward to seeing you in the new year!

To see all scheduled closures for 2025, please see our [**Hours of Operations**](https://www.utm.utoronto.ca/athletics/about-us/hours-operation "Hours of Operation") page.
